🎥: @Detroitlionsnfl

node.text: Browns and RB Nick Chubb reached agreement on a three-year, $36.6 million extension that includes $20 million guaranteed, per source. Chubb will be a free agent again at age 29. Chubb was entering the last year of his contract and opted for a shorter extension, when he can do another deal at 28 years old or become a free agent at 29.

node.text: Former Falcons’ standout Devonta Freeman and the Saints now have reached agreement on a one-year deal, per his agent @agent. Freeman reunited with his former college teammate, Jameis Winston.

node.text:
Melissa Gonzalez, the wife of Lions’ QB David Blough, qualified last night for the Olympic semifinals in the 400 meter hurdles as her husband’s team had an Olympic watch party in Detroit. When she qualified, her husband celebrated, big time.

🎥: @Detroitlionsnfl

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on July 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and people playing football.

node.text: Former All-Pro edge rusher Justin Houston reached agreement on a one-year deal worth up to $4 million with the Baltimore Ravens, per sources. Houston turned down significantly more money from other teams in order to pursue a championship with the Ravens, per source. Houston is coming off 19 sacks in two seasons with the Colts as well as 30 QB hits and a league-high three safeties during 2019 and 2020.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing a sport and outdoors.

node.text:
Colts' QB Carson Wentz is out indefinitely as he undergoes further testing on a foot injury that he suffered at the end of Thursday's practice, per @mikewellsespn and me.

Colts' second-year QB Jacob Eason took the starter reps at today's practice, with Sam Ellinger as his backup.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adam Schefter on July 30, 2021 tagging @dalvincook, @zachiller, and @loyaltyaboveall. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Vikings’ RB Dalvin Cook graduated today from Florida State. He didn’t walk to the podium to receive his Bachelors of Science in interdisciplinary studies/public policy due to training camp practice; instead, Cook put on the gown at his home in Minnesota to bask in his accomplishment.

📸 @dalvincook
